article.headline: UMKC 74, Southern Utah 62
article.story: KANSAS CITY, Mo. (AP) -- Michael Watson scored 31 points in his final regular season home game, leading Missouri-Kansas City to a 74-62 victory over Southern Utah on Thursday night. Fellow senior Javon Clark added 15 points -- all on 3-pointers -- for UMKC (13-13, 8-7 Mid-Continent Conference). Watson connected on a long 3-pointer with 10:45 left in the first half. It was the 379th of his career, one more than Ronnie Schmitz had at UMKC from 1989 through 1993. Watson was 9-of-22 from the field, including 7-of-12 from on 3s. David Palmer was 5-for-11 from beyond the arc and had 25 points for the Thunderbirds (10-16, 6-9), while Jason Baker added 11 points.
